  "prompt": "What are the home prices in Santa Clara, CA?",
  "response": "As of 2023, home prices in Santa Clara, CA, are among the highest in the nation due to its location in the heart of Silicon Valley and the high demand for housing in the area. Here's a general overview of home prices in Santa Clara:\n\n1. **Median Home Price**: The median home price in Santa Clara is typically well over $1 million. As of recent data, it hovers around **$1.4 million to $1.6 million**, depending on the type of home and market conditions.\n\n2. **Single-Family Homes**: Prices for single-family homes in Santa Clara often range from **$1.2 million to $2 million or more**, depending on the size, location, and condition of the property.\n\n3. **Condos and Townhouses**: Condos and townhouses are slightly more affordable, with prices generally ranging from **$800,000 to $1.3 million**.\n\n4. **Luxury Homes**: High-end properties in Santa Clara can easily exceed **$2 million**, with some luxury homes and estates priced at **$3 million or more**.\n\n5. **Market Trends**: Home prices in Santa Clara have seen significant appreciation over the years due to limited inventory and high demand from tech professionals, investors, and buyers seeking proximity to major employers like Google, Apple, and Intel.\n\nFor the most up-to-date and accurate pricing information, it's best to consult real estate platforms like Zillow, Redfin, or Realtor.com, or work with a local real estate agent who can provide insights into current market conditions.",
